---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
const title = "Metabase vs. Power BI";
const description =
  "Metabase is the easier-to-use alternative to Power BI that's super fast to set up. It's the business intelligence tool your team will actually like using.";
const seo = {
  title: "Metabase vs. Power BI",
  description:
    "Metabase is the easier-to-use alternative to Power BI that's super fast to set up. It's the business intelligence tool your team will actually like using.",
  canonical: "/lp/metabase-vs-power-bi",
  og: {
    title: "Metabase vs. Power BI",
    description:
      "Metabase is the easier-to-use alternative to Power BI that's super fast to set up. It's the business intelligence tool your team will actually like using.",
    image: "https://www.metabase.com/images/features/query-builder-og.jpg",
    url: "https://www.metabase.com/lp/metabase-vs-power-bi",
    type: "article",
    site_name:
      "Metabase | Open source Business Intelligence and Embedded Analytics",
  },
  twitter: {
    site: "@metabase",
    title: "Metabase vs. Power BI",
    description:
      "Metabase is the easier-to-use alternative to Power BI that's super fast to set up. It's the business intelligence tool your team will actually like using.",
    card: "summary_large_image",
    image: "https://www.metabase.com/images/features/query-builder-og.jpg",
  },
};
---

<Base {title} {description} {seo}>
  <div class="bootstrap">
    <div class="landing-page">
      <div class="container feature-container landing-page__hero-b">
        <div>
          <h1>Metabase vs. Power BI<br />Which is right for my team?</h1>
          <p>
            Metabase is the easy-to-use business intelligence tool with a
            friendly UX that lets everyone in your team work with data.
          </p>

          <div class="d-flex justify-content-start gap-4">
            <a
              class="fs-13 Button btn btn-primary rounded-3 btn-primary"
              href="https://store.metabase.com/checkout"
            >
              Get started
            </a>

            <a
              class="fs-13 Button btn btn-primary rounded-3 btn-outline-blue"
              href="/talk-to-a-person/"
            >
              Contact us
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="position-relative">
          <iframe
            width="100%"
            height="315"
            src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/xol-cmju3SI"
            title="YouTube video player"
            frameborder="0"
            allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
            referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin"
            allowfullscreen=""></iframe>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="customer-list">
        <div class="d-flex flex-row justify-content-center">
          <p class="paragraph-4-5 neutral-40 my-0 mb-3 py-0">
            <b>Metabase is trusted by over 80,000 companies </b>
          </p>
        </div>

        <a href="/case-studies" class="customer-logos-container">
          <img
            src="/images/logos/Huggingface.svg"
            alt="huggingface logo"
            loading="lazy"
          />

          <img
            src="/images/logos/mcdonalds.svg"
            alt="mcdonalds logo"
            loading="lazy"
          />

          <img src="/images/logos/huma.svg" alt="huma logo" loading="lazy" />

          <img
            src="/images/logos/capital-one.svg"
            alt="capital-one logo"
            loading="lazy"
          />

          <img
            src="/images/logos/home/airbyte.svg"
            alt="airbyte logo"
            loading="lazy"
          />

          <img
            src="/images/logos/betterment.svg"
            alt="betterment logo"
            loading="lazy"
          />

          <img
            src="/images/logos/deutsche-telekom.svg"
            alt="Deutsche Telekom logo"
            loading="lazy"
          />

          <img src="/images/logos/kong.svg" alt="kong logo" loading="lazy" />
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-container flex-row-reverse container">
        <div>
          <h2>What's the difference between Metabase and Power BI</h2>
          <p>
            Power BI has a steeper learning curve than Metabase. People (even
            non-technical or data-savvy folks) actually like using Metabase,
            because it‚Äôs easier to learn, meaning they‚Äôre more likely to run
            reports and get data on their own.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <video
            class="vjs-player lazy w-100 pause-observer autoplay-video"
            autoplay=""
            muted=""
            playsinline=""
            poster="/images/landing-pages/hero-query-builder.gif"
          >
            <source
              src="/images/landing-pages/hero-query-builder.mp4"
              type="video/mp4"
            />

            <p class="vjs-no-js">
              To view this video please enable JavaScript and consider upgrading
              to a web browser that
              <a href="https://videojs.com/html5-video-support/" target="_blank"
                >supports HTML5 video</a
              >
            </p>
          </video>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-container container two-checklists">
        <div>
          <h2>What makes Metabase a good choice compared to Power BI?</h2>
          <p></p>

          <ul class="checklist-outline">
            <li>
              <b>Easy to use for everyone.</b> With intuitive tools like <a
                href="/features/analytics-dashboards">interactive dashboards</a
              > with quick drill-through analyses, the <a
                href="/features/query-builder"
                >query builder to write questions without SQL</a
              >, and one-click-to-create charts.
            </li>

            <li>
              <b>Open source and affordable.</b>
              <a href="/pricing/">Transparent pricing</a> for startups through to
              advanced functionality and support for Enterprise. Secure and scalable,
              with no limits on the size of your dataset.
            </li>

            <li>
              <b
                >Super fast to set up, with simple integration to your preferred
                data tools and OS (e.g., not just Windows and the MS universe)</b
              > Work with your favorite tools, from data sources, transformation,
              ETL, modeling, whether you‚Äôre on Windows, Mac, or Linux.
            </li>

            <li>
              <b>Interactive, customer-facing analytics in days, no sprints.</b>
              <a href="/product/embedded-analytics"
                >Customizable embedded analytics</a
              > that lets your customers explore their data with as much - or as
              little - flexibility as you want.
            </li>

            <li>
              <b>Look and feel.</b> Customers tell us they prefer the look of charts
              and dashboards in Metabase over Power BI. Their teams find them easier
              to understand, and they dig the general vibe.
            </li>

            <li>
              <b>Help from our world class Success team.</b> Technical experts who
              help with everything from troubleshooting to advice on best practices.
              Customers <i>love</i> them.
            </li>

            <li>
              <b>Private and secure.</b>
              <a href="/security">We never look at or copy your data</a>. And we
              prioritize privacy and security features to secure data access in
              your org, like SSO and fine-grained permissions.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2>When might Power BI be a better fit than Metabase?*</h2>
          <p></p>

          <ul class="checklist-outline">
            <li>
              You‚Äôre an enterprise-level company working with large, complex
              data sets, with a dedicated team to run your BI program and ad hoc
              reports for the team.
            </li>

            <li>You only want some people querying your data.</li>

            <li>You‚Äôre not on a budget.</li>

            <li>
              You need all-in-one advanced data integration for data
              transformation and dataflows for ETL processes.
            </li>

            <li>You‚Äôve got time to learn how to use Power BI</li>

            <li>
              You‚Äôre a loyal subject to the Microsoft realm (Mac and Linux fans
              need not apply).
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="testimonial">
        <p>
          <b>*For the record...</b>Metabase also supports a number of happy
          enterprise-level customers for all their BI needs - some even use
          Metabase alongside Power BI to let their less data-savvy teammates
          self-serve analytics and run their own reports. (We‚Äôre trying to
          present a somewhat balanced view here, but c‚Äômon, it‚Äôs still our
          website üòè)
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="testimonial">
        <p>
          ‚ÄúIt's the first time in my years working in data that I saw
          non-technical business users create their own dashboards and analytics
          in our BI platform, all made possible because of Metabase‚Äôs user
          friendly and intuitive data exploration and dashboarding
          capabilities.‚Äù
        </p>

        <p class="author">Dobo Radichkov</p>
        <p class="company">Chief Data Officer, Holland &amp; Barrett</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-container">
        <h4 class="faq-headline">Frequently asked questions</h4>

        <div class="faq">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <div>When is Metabase a better choice than Power BI?</div>
            <img alt="Chevron Blue" src="/images/chevron_blue.svg" width="14" />
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div>
              <p>
                Metabase is best suited for businesses that need a
                straightforward way for everyone in the team to self-serve
                analytics. Metabase is the business intelligence platform that
                your team will actually enjoy using, at the right price for your
                scale.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-question">
            <div>When is Power BI a better choice than Metabase?</div>
            <img alt="Chevron Blue" src="/images/chevron_blue.svg" width="14" />
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div>
              <p>
                Credit where it‚Äôs due - Power BI can be a good fit for larger
                enterprises or orgs with more extensive data analysis needs,
                deep pockets, and a lower need for everyone in the org to be
                able to jump in and run their own reports. It‚Äôs got all the
                bells and whistles - and depending on the maturity of your org,
                your use case and needs, it may be more than you need.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-question">
            <div>Who uses Metabase over Power BI?</div>
            <img alt="Chevron Blue" src="/images/chevron_blue.svg" width="14" />
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div>
              <p>
                Metabase is trusted by over 80,000 companies with their
                analytics, from startups who need their first business
                intelligence tool through to Enterprises. Metabase open source
                is the go-to choice for founders and solo-developers to let
                their teams get answers from data on their own so they‚Äôre not
                running the same reports once a month. Metabase Pro and
                Enterprise is generally chosen by CTOs, CPOs, Heads of Data who
                have been there, done that with every other BI tool on the
                market and need a way to make self-service analytics <i
                  >actually</i
                > happen.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-question">
            <div>What use cases do Metabase and Power BI cover?</div>
            <img alt="Chevron Blue" src="/images/chevron_blue.svg" width="14" />
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div>
              <p>
                Metabase and Power BI both cater to internal analytics, as well
                as interactive embedded analytics for customers.
              </p><p>
                Metabase is ideal for quick, intuitive data exploration that
                lets people in your company click around in interactive
                dashboard and visualizations to learn from data, or create
                queries with or without SQL.
              </p><p>
                Power BI may be better suited for complex data analysis and
                putting detailed visualizations in front of customers.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-question">
            <div>
              What‚Äôs the differences in pricing between Metabase and Power BI?
            </div>
            <img alt="Chevron Blue" src="/images/chevron_blue.svg" width="14" />
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div>
              <p>
                Metabase is open source with affordable plans available for
                additional security and governance features, cloud deployment,
                and fast, unlimited technical help from engineers.
              </p><p>
                Power BI's pricing is generally higher with user-based licensing
                with various pricing tiers depending on the use case.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-question">
            <div>Do you need to know SQL to use Metabase or Power BI?</div>
            <img alt="Chevron Blue" src="/images/chevron_blue.svg" width="14" />
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div>
              <p>
                Metabase and Power BI both let data analysts work in SQL; and
                less technically savvy people ask questions without SQL.
              </p><p></p><p>
                Metabase's intuitive Query Builder lets non-technical or data
                savvy people put together analyses with clicks - no SQL
                necessary. Analysts and data people who prefer to write SQL can
                fill their boots in the SQL editor.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-question">
            <div>
              How do Metabase and Power BI compare in terms of visualization
              capabilities?
            </div>
            <img alt="Chevron Blue" src="/images/chevron_blue.svg" width="14" />
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div>
              <p>
                Metabase and Power BI give people a way to visualize their data
                and make sense of the numbers. But Metabase is so much more than
                just a visualization tool. For people who feel like they‚Äôre
                seeing double when staring at columns, it‚Äôs an intuitive way to
                filter and summarize to uncover trends and get insights to make
                data-driven decisions.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="faq-question">
            <div>
              Ok, give it to me straight though - what‚Äôs the best Business
              Intelligence tool?
            </div>
            <img alt="Chevron Blue" src="/images/chevron_blue.svg" width="14" />
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div>
              <p>
                There‚Äôs no right or wrong answer here. It will generally depend
                on your use case, how much you want people to be able to learn
                from data and run reports on their own without depending on your
                data team; your preferred data stack, how fast you need to get
                up and running, your budget, and more.
              </p><p>
                If you‚Äôre curious about how other BI tools compare, check out
                our <a href="/blog/metabase-alternatives"
                  >Metabase Alternatives</a
                > post, where we explore how Metabase stacks up against other options.
              </p><p>
                Again, there‚Äôs no ‚Äúright‚Äù answer, but just sayin‚Äô - Metabase
                will let everyone on your team work with data, integrates with
                your preferred data tools, gets up and running in 5 minutes
                flat, and suits all budgets (and you can try it for free).
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bootstrap">
          <div class="faq-contact-us">
            <div>
              <svg
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                width="24"
                height="24"
                fill="none"
                ><path
                  stroke="#509EE3"
                  stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-linejoin="round"
                  stroke-width="1.5"
                  d="M4.75 6.75a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10.5a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v7.5a2 2 0 0 1-2 2h-2.625l-2.625 3-2.625-3H6.75a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-7.5Z"
                ></path><path
                  stroke="#509EE3"
                  stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-linejoin="round"
                  d="M9.5 11a.5.5 0 1 1-1 0 .5.5 0 0 1 1 0ZM12.5 11a.5.5 0 1 1-1 0 .5.5 0 0 1 1 0ZM15.5 11a.5.5 0 1 1-1 0 .5.5 0 0 1 1 0Z"
                ></path></svg
              >

              Have more questions? We‚Äôd be happy to help.
            </div>
            <a
              class="fs-13 Button btn btn-primary rounded-3 ms-lg-2"
              href="/talk-to-a-person/"
            >
              Talk to a person
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <section
        class="m-0 mb-15 mb-lg-20 mx-auto p-0 center-xs container landing-page__ctas"
      >
        <h2 class="fs-8 fw-bold mx-auto my-0">Learn more about Metabase</h2>

        <div
          class="align-stretch d-flex flex-column flex-lg-row flex-nowrap gap-6 gap-lg-8 justify-content-between mt-8 mt-lg-13 ctas__cards"
        >
          <a
            class="bg-white border--blue-95 box-shadow-xs d-block m-0 p-4 p-lg-6 rounded-4 text-left ctas__cards__card"
            href="/learn/cheat-sheets/transition-guides/powerbi-to-metabase"
            title="Transition cheat sheet - A smooth move from Power BI to Metabase"
          >
            <span
              class="bg-blue-95 blue-60 d-inline-block fs-15 fw-bolder m-0 px-3 py-2 rounded-3 text-uppercase"
              >Transition cheat sheet</span
            >
            <h3 class="fs-10 fw-bold lh-base m-0 mt-4">
              A smooth move from Power BI to Metabase
            </h3>
          </a>

          <a
            class="bg-white border--blue-95 box-shadow-xs d-block m-0 p-4 p-lg-6 rounded-4 text-left ctas__cards__card"
            href="/demo"
            title="Video demo - From zero to dashboard in 5 minutes"
          >
            <span
              class="bg-blue-95 blue-60 d-inline-block fs-15 fw-bolder m-0 px-3 py-2 rounded-3 text-uppercase"
              >Video demo</span
            >
            <h3 class="fs-10 fw-bold lh-base m-0 mt-4">
              From zero to dashboard in 5 minutes
            </h3>
          </a>

          <a
            class="bg-white border--blue-95 box-shadow-xs d-block m-0 p-4 p-lg-6 rounded-4 text-left ctas__cards__card"
            href="/events/metabase-for-beginners"
            title="Webinar - A tour of Metabase for beginners"
          >
            <span
              class="bg-blue-95 blue-60 d-inline-block fs-15 fw-bolder m-0 px-3 py-2 rounded-3 text-uppercase"
              >Webinar</span
            >
            <h3 class="fs-10 fw-bold lh-base m-0 mt-4">
              A tour of Metabase for beginners
            </h3>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="try-metabase-footer">
        <div class="full-width-centered">
          <h3>Try Metabase Starter 14 days free</h3>
          <p>Pay as you go, or get 10% off with an annual subscription.</p>
          <a
            id="get-started-btn-home"
            class="fs-13 Button btn btn-primary rounded-3 ms-lg-2"
            href="https://store.metabase.com/checkout"
          >
            Get started
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="light-blue-footer-container">
        <div class="bootstrap"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
